PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1468-0262.00465
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - With cheap talk, more can be achieved by long conversations than by a single message?even when one side is strictly better informed than the other. (?Cheap talk? means plain conversation?unmediated, nonbinding, and payoff-irrelevant.) This work characterizes the equilibrium payoffs for all two-person games in which one side is better informed than the other and cheap talk is permitted.
ER  - 

